dcterms:description: Graphs derived from the Web graph provided by Common Crawl, where the nodes are hostnames and the edges are the hyperlinks between these websites. The original graph has 385 million nodes and 2.5 billion edges, which is too large to be loaded into memory, so subgraphs of 200,000 websites are constructed.
dcterms:title: WWW-200K

dcterms:description: A network between the users on the photo sharing website Flickr. The labels represent the interest groups a user joins.
